apps/ -- the application layer
==============================

This tree was reorganised from a flat ~95-file directory into the layout below.
The full rationale, the file-by-file mapping and the verification method are in
.specifications/REFACTOR_PROPOSAL.md; this file is the short version you need in
order to find things and to put new code in the right place.


Layout
------

  main.c, root_menu.c/.h    Startup and top-level navigation. The only code
                            that belongs to no single domain.

  -- the device --
  audio/        The playback pipeline: playback, pcmbuf, buffering, codecs,
                the codec and audio threads, voice, beep, A-B repeat.
  database/     The tag database: tagcache, tagtree.
  playlist/     Playlists in memory and on disk, plus the playlist viewer
                and catalog.
  metadata/     Per-track data: album art and its cache, cuesheets, multi-file
                ID3 aggregation.

  -- the interface, by altitude --
  draw/         Stateless drawing. Knows pixels; knows nothing about features.
                viewport, line, scrollbar, icon, bmp, resize, jpeg decode,
                screen_access.
  widgets/      Reusable controls. Called by someone else, hand control back.
                list, dialog, yesno, splash, option_select, colour picker,
                folder select, keyboard, menu, text_box, meters.
  screens/      Full screens. Navigated TO; run their own loop until the user
                leaves. wps, browser, context menu, quickscreen, bookmarks,
                track info, debug menu, cover flow, and menus/ (the settings
                menu tree).
  viewers/      File-format applications: their own model, view and input.
                text_viewer/ (streaming document engine), image_viewer/,
                properties, playing_time, credits.
  skin/         The skin interpreter, backdrops, and the skinned status bar.

  -- services --
  settings/     The settings model and its table.
  input/        Buttons, actions, keymaps.
  speech/       Voice output and translation.
  system/       Cross-cutting glue: shutdown and system events, the activity
                stack, string/path helpers, time formatting, volume,
                and app_util (assorted small UI helpers).

  -- boundaries --
  iap/          Apple accessory protocol.
  api/          The headers that firmware/ and lib/ include by name. READ
                api/README before touching anything here.

  -- pinned by the build system, not by code --
  bitmaps/      tools/root.make:70
  lang/         tools/root.make:129, tools/configure:1424
  plugins/      Contains no plugin. tools/root.make:134-135 and
                tools/buildzip.pl:497,550 name these paths, and plugin.lds is
                the LIVE codec linker script. See plugins/README.


Where does new code go?
-----------------------

The distinction that does the most work is draw -> widgets -> screens ->
viewers. Apply it in that order:

  Does it put pixels somewhere it was handed, with no input loop and no
  knowledge of what it is drawing for?              -> draw/
  Is it called by something else, and does it hand
  control back when done (a question, a picker)?    -> widgets/
  Is it navigated to, owning the screen until the
  user leaves?                                      -> screens/
  Does it also own a file format and a document
  model?                                            -> viewers/

Everything else goes by subject matter: audio code in audio/, settings code in
settings/, and so on. If a file would land in system/, stop and check whether
it really belongs to a domain -- system/ is the residue, not the default.


Conventions
-----------

Includes are written relative to apps/:

    #include "widgets/splash.h"      not "splash.h"
    #include "draw/viewport.h"       not "viewport.h"

Same-directory includes stay bare. The include path is deliberately only
apps/ and apps/api (see apps.make); it is NOT taken from tools/configure's
APPEXTRA, which is stale. Angle brackets are for firmware/ and lib/ headers
only -- <> does not search the including file's directory, so a local header
included that way breaks as soon as it moves.

Declare what you use. A file that uses HZ should include kernel.h, even if it
currently compiles without it because some other header drags it in. Several
files still rely on that kind of luck; section 9.3 of the proposal has the
counts. Every header move so far has broken a few apparently unrelated files
because of it.

Files that were moved or renamed carry their original location on line 1:

    /* was: apps/gui/statusbar-skinned.c */

That is permanent, and `grep -rn '^/\* was:'` is the whole move manifest.


Two things that will surprise you
---------------------------------

fracmul.h sits at the apps/ root rather than in system/ where it belongs.
lib/rbcodec/codecs/spc.c includes "../fracmul.h", and a "../" include resolves
against each -I directory rather than by name, so no file inside api/ can
satisfy it. lib/ is outside this fork's editable scope.

tagnavi.config sits at the apps/ root rather than in database/. tools/buildzip.pl
reads that exact path, and buildzip.pl is kept byte-identical to upstream.
